    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\n### What was explored\n- All 4 existing format object files: `TOMLObject.zig` (parse-only), `JSONCObject.zig` (parse-only), `JSON5Object.zig` (parse+stringify), `YAMLObject.zig` (parse+stringify)\n- The full wiring chain: `BunObject.zig` → `api.zig` → `BunObject+exports.h` → `BunObject.cpp` → `bun.d.ts`\n- The internal INI parser in `src/ini.zig` (which we will **not** import per requirements)\n- Exact JSValue APIs used by each implementation (`putMayBeIndex`, `wtf.StringBuilder`, `JSPropertyIterator`, etc.)\n\n### 6 files to change\n\n1. **Create `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — Self-contained `create`/`parse`/`stringify`. Parse builds JSValues line-by-line (sections → nested objects, key=value with whitespace trim, `#`/`;` comments, type coercion for `true`/`false`/`null`/numbers). Stringify uses `wtf.StringBuilder` + `JSPropertyIterator` (scalars first, then `[section]` headers for object values).\n\n2. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** — Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n\n3. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — Add lazy property constant, `@export`, getter function `getINIObject`, and import — all following the exact same patterns as `TOML`/`JSON5`/`YAML`.\n\n4. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — Add `macro(INI) \\` between `macro(Glob)` and `macro(JSON5)` (alphabetical order).\n\n5. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — Add `INI    BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI    DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to `bunObjectTable` between `Glob` and `JSONC`.\n\n6. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — Add `namespace INI` with full JSDoc for `parse(input: string): Record<string, any>` and `stringify(input: Record<string, any>): string`.",
